Your userId is the part that identifies your offline device. It is your very secret and is not intended to be shared without cautions.
If you leak your userId on the internet the chats with your chat partners can easily be attacked.
When both userIds are leaked the whole communication can be decrypted when the messages are available too.
Your UserId contains your nickname, a part of the symmetric key and an asymmetric key which are needed to identify yourself and encrypt the whole communication.
The userId also contains your onlineId when you are using the google api, so the sent messages are directed to your online device.
It is really important to keep this as a secret. Do not deliver it on any insecure channel also it is secured by a short passphrase when displayed.
The securest option is to just share it via your camera when both chat partners are physically next to each other!